284	 * for the first time, we convert it to OBJ_ENCODING_LISTPACK_EX encoding.
285	 * We allocate "struct listpackEx" which holds listpack pointer and expiry
286	 * metadata. In the listpack string, we append another TTL entry for each field
287	 * value pair. From now on, listpack will have triplets in it: field-value-ttl.
288	 * If TTL is not set for a field, we store 'zero' as the TTL value. 'zero' is
289	 * encoded as two bytes in the listpack. Memory overhead of a non-existing TTL
290	 * will be two bytes per field.
291	 *
292	 * Fields in the listpack will be ordered by TTL. Field with the smallest expiry
293	 * time will be the first item. Fields without TTL will be at the end of the
294	 * listpack. This way, it is easier/faster to find expired items.
